<row>
<entry valign="top" align="left">1. Identify learning needs</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00003"><item>Complete a community health needs assessment and prioritize health problems and educational needs</item>
<item>Complete a learner assessment that includes motivation, abilities, health literacy, culture, and other learner needs</item>
</list>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="top" align="left">2. Establish goals and objectives</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00004"><item>Finalize the goals of the educational program</item>
<item>Finalize SMART objectives</item>
</list>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="top" align="left">3. Select appropriate education methods</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00005"><item>Select learning theory</item>
<item>Determine teaching strategies and learning format</item>
<item>Examine and reduce possible educational issues</item>
